review_blob:
Nice copper color with off white creamy head. Little aroma but a slight tartness (berry like). Creamy mouthfeel. Tartness is balanced with malt. Bitterness is in check. Flavor is almost strawberry. No alcohol bite at all. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Aroma not as pronounced as I expected
Low head with nice clear Amber-copper color. Nice balance with malt/bitterness but hop aroma and flavor are less pronounced than I would like. May be aged a bit. Not bad but is probably not representative of what the beer tastes like fresh. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
